From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Paul Philippov <paul@themactep.com>
Date: Wed, 2 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] remove __fgetc_unlocked/__fputc_unlocked shim (uclibc provides them)

The shim defines __fgetc_unlocked and __fputc_unlocked to satisfy
Ingenic libimp library dependencies.  However, uClibc-ng already
exports these functions as global symbols:

  00048f70 g  __fgetc_unlocked
  00049210 g  __fputc_unlocked

The shim's definitions shadow uClibc-ng's, causing symbol interposition
that creates an infinite recursion cycle:

  shim::__fgetc_unlocked -> uclibc::fgetc -> shim::__fgetc_unlocked

(because uclibc's fgetc internally branches to __fgetc_unlocked).

Fix: remove the redundant shim definitions entirely so uClibc-ng's
native implementations are used directly.  No dlsym tricks needed.

Signed-off-by: Paul Philippov <paul@themactep.com>

--- a/uclibc_shim.c
+++ b/uclibc_shim.c
@@ -36,10 +36,8 @@ void __assert(const char *msg, const char *file, int line) {
 	abort();
 }
 
-int __fgetc_unlocked(FILE *stream) {
-	DEBUG_PRINT(stderr, "[WARNING] Called __fgetc_unlocked. This is a shim and does nothing.\n");
-	return fgetc(stream);
-}
+/* uClibc-ng already exports __fgetc_unlocked and __fputc_unlocked —
+   do not redefine them here. */
 
 // Custom mmap implementations address an Ingenic library bug affecting memory mapping offsets.
 // Using musl, the library requires specific handling of offsets, necessitating these workarounds.
@@ -63,10 +61,7 @@ void *mmap(void *start, size_t len, int prot, int flags, int fd, uint32_t off) {
 
 /* Required for Xburst2 libraries */
 
-int __fputc_unlocked(int c, FILE *stream) {
-	DEBUG_PRINT(stderr, "[WARNING] Called __fputc_unlocked. This is a shim and does nothing.\n");
-	return fputc(c, stream);
-}
+/* uClibc-ng already provides __fputc_unlocked — removed. */
 
 #undef fopen
 FILE* fopen64(const char *path, const char *mode) {
